cova.data

Class WrappedAccessPath

  • java.lang.Object
    • cova.data.WrappedAccessPath

  • public class WrappedAccessPath
extends Object
    The Class WrappedAccessPath represents the access path of a taint object. An access path can be a base, a static field or based followed by instance fields.

      • copyFields

        public WrappedAccessPath copyFields(soot.Local param)
        This method is used to map the taints as arguments at caller site taints to taints as parameter at callee site. eg. the access path at the caller is a.b.c.field, the parameter is d. If d and b have the same data type, then the access path at the callee is d.c.field.
        Parameters:
        param - parameter of callee method, it can only be local.
        Returns:
        a new access path at the callee
        See Also:
        rules.GeneralPropagationRule

      • replacePrefix

        public WrappedAccessPath replacePrefix(WrappedAccessPath accessPath,
                                       int prefixLength)
        This method replace the prefix of this access path with given access path e.g. Assume this access path is a.b.c, prefixLength is 2, given access path is d.e, then the return access path is d.e.c.
        Parameters:
        accessPath - the acessPath which replaces the prefix
        prefixLength - the length of the prefix to be replaced
        Returns:
        access path whose prefix with given length is replaced by the given value.
